{"TopicId":198810,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"[Modded] The ADFX-02 Morgan","CreatedByName":"Kerburettor","CreatedById":194580,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-18T11:33:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerburettor","CreatedById":194580,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-18T11:33:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recreated this fictional aircraft from the Ace Combat series using several mods including FARc, BD Armory, the B9 Aerospace package, TweakScale and Airplane plus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESupermaneuverability:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis plane is supermaneuverable in the 120 m/s - 200 m/s velocity range and has weapons similar to their strangereal equivalents:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2*AIM-120 AMRAAM Missiles (MSL)\u003Cbr\u003E\n2*JDAM Bomb (MPBM)\u003Cbr\u003E\n1*\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E/ALQ-131 ECM jammer (IEWS)\u003Cbr\u003E\n1*USAF Airborn Laser (TLS)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe airframe can withstand an estimated 11.3 g under 2 km but it has been shown that sharp maneuvers above a dynamic pressure of 50 kPa (approx 325 m/s @ 1.1 km)\u00A0 regularly causes canard failure.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis video shows how much yaw authority matters when it comes to controlling sideslip-induced roll during post-stall maneuvers:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/C-ffhkVNeRw?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt